1
00:01:16,319 --> 00:01:16,959
Who is it?

2
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,719
It's me, Meiduo.

3
00:01:19,959 --> 00:01:20,719
Come on in.

4
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:25,719
Don't move.

5
00:01:25,719 --> 00:01:26,480
Sit down, sit down.

6
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,159
What do you need?

7
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:33,400
Hurry, put this on.

8
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,319
Zhaxi spent two hours brewing this for you.

9
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:36,760
Where is he?

10
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,439
He shoved it at me and ran off.

11
00:01:38,719 --> 00:01:39,680
Like he was guilty of something.

12
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,640
He said he went into the woods.

13
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:46,760
This late?

14
00:01:47,359 --> 00:01:48,000
What's he doing there?

15
00:01:48,319 --> 00:01:48,959
He said...

16
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:50,599
if he can't save that Gastrodia,

17
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:52,120
he's too ashamed to face you.

18
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:56,680
Tell me,

19
00:01:57,159 --> 00:01:58,280
that guy,

20
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,560
isn't he just a fool?

21
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,000
He really is kind of dumb.

22
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,359
Not just dumb,

23
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:04,400
also clueless.

24
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:05,959
Just like a big yak.

25
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,560
Talking about yaks like that,

26
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:10,759
would the yaks agree?

27
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:13,840
Sis,

28
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:17,520
what if he gets lost in the mountains?

29
00:02:17,719 --> 00:02:19,280
What if he runs into a bear?

30
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,599
What if he falls into the swamp?

31
00:02:22,319 --> 00:02:23,039
Stop with the "what ifs."

32
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,199
Sis,

33
00:02:28,599 --> 00:02:29,479
do you miss him?

34
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:31,560
I mean,

35
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,039
do you want him back soon?

36
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:35,680
He can come back or not, I don't care.

37
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:44,319
Well, I'll get going then.

38
00:02:48,599 --> 00:02:50,319
Remember to put the medicine on.

39
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:50,919
Okay.

40
00:02:51,479 --> 00:02:52,240
Get some rest.

41
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,120
Bye.

42
00:03:01,759 --> 00:03:02,919
Even yaks know their way home.

43
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,120
Zhaxi

44
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:40,800
How is it?

45
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,719
I don't dare touch it.

46
00:04:02,719 --> 00:04:03,680
The flavor is back.

47
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,560
The mycelium has reconnected to the veins.

48
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:08,840
Zhaxi!

49
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:10,120
It's alive!

50
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:15,840
It's alive!

51
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,000
You scared me to death.

52
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:20,680
That's wonderful!

53
00:04:20,879 --> 00:04:21,839
It's so good that it survived!

54
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,639
I was scared half to death.

55
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,680
It's okay, it's okay, it's okay.

56
00:04:26,639 --> 00:04:27,360
As long as it's alive, that's all that matters.

57
00:04:58,439 --> 00:05:00,279
I just got a little too excited.

58
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,800
It's fine, it's fine.

59
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:16,360
I meant, help me pick up my hiking pole.

60
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,480
I thought it was...

61
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,079
Thought what?

62
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:22,920
Don't go thinking anything.

63
00:05:23,639 --> 00:05:24,680
No, I was just...

64
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:25,720
Don't go imagining things either.

65
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,319
Your leg's not healed yet, slow down.

66
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:25,480
That spinach grew so tall!

67
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:28,680
Fifty-nine.

68
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:34,720
Forty-six.

69
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,160
Are you sleepy?

70
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,160
The brand is suspending our partnership.

71
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:53,279
The termination letter goes out tomorrow.

72
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:56,040
Someone like you, who won't even honor family,

73
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,720
poses too much risk to commercial value.

74
00:06:58,279 --> 00:06:59,160
You're on your own now.

75
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:00,800
Nana.

76
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,480
Where are you going?

77
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,040
None of your business.

78
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:08,560
Aren't you doing our e-commerce training?

79
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,560
Everyone's ready.

80
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,839
We're just waiting for your class.

81
00:07:12,199 --> 00:07:13,240
When does it start?

82
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:22,279
You still dare to keep me here?

83
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,560
After how I acted in that livestream?

84
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:29,199
There are some things

85
00:07:30,319 --> 00:07:31,160
you just don't understand.

86
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:34,279
That line of yours

87
00:07:35,519 --> 00:07:36,360
hurts worse than cursing me out.

88
00:07:37,959 --> 00:07:38,759
Would cursing you do any good?

89
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:40,759
Nana!

90
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:42,040
Nana!

91
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:42,839
Dr. Meiduo.

92
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,160
What are you running out here for?

93
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,040
I came after you.

94
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,759
That e-commerce deal you signed with the village,

95
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:51,360
I read it.

96
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,959
If you leave now, you'll owe damages.

97
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,759
And the contract clearly states

98
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:57,879
it's e-commerce services plus follow-up training.

99
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,800
You haven't done the e-commerce service,

100
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,879
nor the follow-up training.

101
00:08:01,759 --> 00:08:02,759
What are you talking about?

102
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,279
I never signed anything

103
00:08:04,279 --> 00:08:05,639
about any follow-up service contract.

104
00:08:06,639 --> 00:08:07,360
Are you sure?

105
00:08:07,879 --> 00:08:08,879
Why don't you think again?

106
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,000
Just kidding.

107
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:18,680
There's no penalty fee at all.

108
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,839
Dr. Meiduo, I...

109
00:08:20,319 --> 00:08:21,240
My foot hurts.

110
00:08:29,199 --> 00:08:30,199
What's the point of me staying?

111
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:32,960
Netizens are bashing me.

112
00:08:34,399 --> 00:08:35,440
My agent's chewing me out too.

113
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,879
And now even the villagers

114
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,080
are probably sick of me.

115
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:42,919
I'm not sick of you.

116
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,559
Me neither.

117
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,200
And Zhaxi too.

118
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,440
Is Zhaxi sick of you?

119
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,559
He even said yesterday...

120
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,480
What did he say?

121
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:55,320
He said the way you did that livestream

122
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,399
had real personality.

123
00:08:57,799 --> 00:08:58,879
Is that a compliment?

124
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,519
You don't know him.

125
00:09:01,879 --> 00:09:03,320
For him to say something like that,

126
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,360
that counts as high praise.

127
00:09:07,559 --> 00:09:08,120
Nana.

128
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,200
Please don't leave.

129
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,320
Everyone's waiting for you.

130
00:09:13,759 --> 00:09:14,919
Waiting for you to teach us.

131
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:20,919
Well,

132
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:23,159
is there still a breach penalty?

133
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,279
No.

134
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,159
But I can't guarantee

135
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,600
that if you really do leave,

136
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:31,519
Zhang Haoran won't sneak one in himself.

137
00:09:33,759 --> 00:09:34,360
Fine.

138
00:09:35,159 --> 00:09:37,080
Then I'll stay a couple of days.

139
00:09:37,759 --> 00:09:39,120
Forget the catchphrases.

140
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,840
Forget "lowest price online."

141
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,200
City folks these days,

142
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:43,720
crammed on subways, eating takeout,

143
00:09:44,039 --> 00:09:45,960
they don't care how durable the fabric is.

144
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,000
What they want is that buying this fabric

145
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,279
will give them a poetic life.

146
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:52,720
That's what we call selling dreams.

147
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:58,799
Zhuoma,

148
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,120
come over here for a sec.

149
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:08,919
Now,

150
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:11,039
let's pretend we're weaving.

151
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:16,320
Slow down your movements.

152
00:10:16,679 --> 00:10:17,519
Make it more elegant.

153
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,720
Don't look at the camera.

154
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:23,960
Look out the window.

155
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:29,200
Give that "I'm waiting for the wind,

156
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,720
waiting for you" melancholy vibe.

157
00:10:32,679 --> 00:10:36,200
But weaving needs eyes on the shuttle.

158
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:38,639
If I look outside, the threads tangle.

159
00:10:38,879 --> 00:10:41,000
And you can't slow down either.

160
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,679
Slow down and the fabric won't be tight.

161
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:43,960
Zhuoma,

162
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,240
who cares if the fabric's tight?

163
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,679
Netizens want visuals,

164
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:49,679
they want atmosphere,

165
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,759
and these hands of yours.

166
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:55,000
These are a craftsman's badge of honor.

167
00:10:57,759 --> 00:10:59,960
But we can't shoot this cut directly.

168
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:02,799
It'd make people feel it's too bitter.

169
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:04,159
Qianqian,

170
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,279
let's set up a rim light.

171
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:21,960
Sis.

172
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:23,720
Turn your head toward the window.

173
00:11:24,759 --> 00:11:25,120
Good.

174
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:26,639
Smile.

175
00:11:28,519 --> 00:11:29,200
Yes, don't move.

176
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:34,360
Look.

177
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,879
With this rim light, it looks beautiful.

178
00:11:37,639 --> 00:11:39,320
And then pair it with

179
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,320
some ethereal guqin music.

180
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:43,840
So even though you're spacing out,

181
00:11:44,039 --> 00:11:47,519
it feels like you're in dialogue with time.

182
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:51,000
This isn't me.

183
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:53,679
Sister Zhuoma.

184
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:54,799
Hold this.

185
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,399
The people in here,

186
00:12:01,519 --> 00:12:02,360
their faces are smooth,

187
00:12:02,879 --> 00:12:03,679
their hands are soft.

188
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,080
It looks like they're performing.

189
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:08,000
But our real intangible heritage

190
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,799
is every single person you see here.

191
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:12,919
When we weave,

192
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:14,559
we sit until our backs ache.

193
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:16,759
Every one of us has

194
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,399
bloody cuts from the threads on our hands.

195
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:22,159
To count every single thread,

196
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:25,480
even when our eyes blur,

197
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,519
we still push through.

198
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,360
This is the real us.

199
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,080
Sister Zhuoma.

200
00:12:30,759 --> 00:12:31,960
Of course authenticity matters.

201
00:12:32,279 --> 00:12:33,600
But it doesn't sell for a good price.

202
00:12:34,679 --> 00:12:36,440
Pointing that cut at the camera,

203
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:38,279
that's not selling products.

204
00:12:38,559 --> 00:12:39,320
That's selling misery.

205
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,440
Just think about it.

206
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,279
What do netizens want to see now?

207
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:49,480
Dreams and faraway places.

208
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,399
I'm doing this for everyone's sake.

209
00:12:54,279 --> 00:12:54,840
Nana.

210
00:12:57,039 --> 00:12:57,720
Maybe

211
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,919
you understand people online better,

212
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,919
but you don't understand this cloth.

213
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,360
This pulu

214
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,960
is what we tie around our waists against the cold.

215
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,960
It's not a dream hanging on a wall.

216
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,480
If, just to sell goods,

217
00:13:12,039 --> 00:13:13,360
you make every one of us

218
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,679
pretend to be detached from the real world,

219
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:17,960
then this cloth loses its soul.

220
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:21,240
I won't act.

221
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,519
Sister Zhuoma.
